He first joined Swansea for a month in the 2010-11 campaign, scoring twice in five appearances. Last season, he made nine appearances and scored once after joining on loan in January.

Swans are also discussing a possible deal for Ferencvaros midfielder Muhamed Besic. The 21-year-old Bosnia international impressed during the World Cup and is available for £3m.

Meanwhile, The Welsh club say they want £45million for Wilfried Bony, Michel Vorm and Ben Davies who have attracted interest from Tottenham and Liverpool.

Spurs have opened talks over Davies but Swansea value him at £12m while striker Bony is now rated at £25m and Vorm around £8m.

